The Telegraph - Calcutta (Kolkata) | Sports | DAY IV HIGHLIGHTS
                                                                                                                       7                                      DAY IV HIGHLIGHTS
                      
	SACHIN TENDULKAR (203)               
	On 143, Sachin Tendulkar became the first visiting player to score 1000 runs on Sri Lankan soil. Tendulkar now has 1060 runs in Sri Lanka.         
	On 144, Sachin registered his highest score on Sri Lankan soil. His previous highest was 143 in August 1997 in Colombo (RPS).         
	When he brought up his 19th 150-plus score in Tests, Sachin equalled West Indian Brian Laras record of most 150-plus scores in Test cricket. He left behind Don Bradman who has 18 such scores.         
	 On 200, Sachin Tendulkar scored his fifth double hundred in Test cricket. His last double (248*) came vs Bangladesh in Dhaka, December 2004.         
	 On 200, Sachin Tendulkar became the only fourth visiting player and second Indian to score a double hundred on Sri Lankan soil. It may be recalled Sehwag had scored 201* in Galle in 2008.         
	 On 202, Sachin registered the highest score by an Indian on Sri Lankan soil, bettering Sehwags 201* in Galle in 2008.                 
	SURESH RAINA (120)               
	 Suresh Raina became the ninth Indian and 59th player overall to score a century in his debut innings in Test cricket. The last player to do so was Virender Sehwag (105) vs South Africa in Bloemfontein 2001-02         
	 Interestingly Raina, who made a century on Test debut, also made his ODI debut against Sri Lanka in Dambulla on 30 July 2005, and scored a first-ball duck.         
	 With this century Suresh Raina becomes the first Indian and fourth player in the world to score a hundred in all three forms of the game. The others are Chris Gayle, Brendon McCullum and Mahela Jayawardene.               
	PARTNERSHIP (256)               
	 On 150, the duo equalled the best partnership for the fifth wicket by India against Sri Lanka. The previous best involved Sachin and Sourav Ganguly (150, Colombo, SSC,1997-98).         
	The duo also bettered the best-ever fifth-wicket partnership on this ground, which was 150 by Sachin-Sourav (150, Colombo, SSC,1997-98).         
	 On 175, the Sachin-Raina partnership bettered the previous best fifth wicket partnership against Lanka in Tests. The previous best being174 by Younis Khan amp; Faisal Iqbal, Karachi, 2008-09.           COMPILED BY MOHANDAS MENON                                                                                                                 
